{
  "info": {
    "name": "AI4W-ABL Channel Integration (ABLP-420)",
    "description": "Tests the ai4w channel endpoints introduced in ABLP-420.\n\n**Setup**:\n1. Import the companion environment file (ai4w-abl-postman-environment.json) and pick it.\n2. In the environment, set: `baseUrl`, `serviceToken`, `jwt`, `tenantId`, `projectId`, `userEmail`.\n3. Run **Provision Connection** first — it writes `connectionId` + `connectionSecret` into the environment automatically.\n4. You can then run any Public Channel request — the folder-level pre-request script HMAC-signs automatically.\n\n**JWT minting**: The `jwt` env var must be a valid short-lived AI4W JWT with `email`, `accountId`, `iss=AI4W_JWT_ISSUER`, `aud=AI4W_JWT_AUDIENCE`. Mint it outside Postman (Postman's sandbox doesn't include RS256 JWT signing).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "ai4w-abl-ablp-420-v1"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3112",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "ABL runtime base URL (no trailing slash)"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
